<br>
However, what is the latest Conventional Wisdom on getting flagged in PoP?  I am thinking mroe in a sense for PoS/PoV, but I was also thinking about the Factory in PoI and the hedge in PoN (nice exp in there and open 99% of the time).  <br>
<br>
I tried a couple times to get flagged in PoJ, once with an AoE group and once with a regular group.  The regular group sucked cause we had some peeps under level 60 so our dps just was not there.  <br>
<br>
On the Aoe group we did much better, only to get to the Executioner once to find out that our casters were oom, and the cleric had to CH twice while they were medding then I died.  <br>
<br>
How high does a Warrior have to be in relation to AC, HPs, ATK to get flagged?  What is the standard procedure outside of gettin &quot;pushed&quot; through by friends.  <br>
<br>
I currently am level 60, have mostly Thurg armor, Dual Wield FG and Frostbringer, have run3, regen3, and now ND1 for aa's.  Personally I think I am too weak and am working on ND3 at the minimum before I try again.  <br>
<br>
What do I need to work on to get flagged?  How do other warriors get flagged?  Should I try to get flagged for the Hedge in PoN for now to get much better exp 'till I get decent aa's? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gallerus>Gallerus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 187<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/24/03 12:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Latest CW On Flagging</span><hr size=1> hedge flag is irrelevant really - its only purpose is to get you into ponb which is only good if you are in a guild that is capable of killing terris thule (prolly 24-30 people with decent levels + gear could do it).<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.cox.net/mherlihy/img/gallerus.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=412980" target="top">Lorcann</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->   <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=412968" target="top">Gallerus</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->   <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=413004" target="top">Borstal</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=farlanderb>FarlanderB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 108<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/24/03 12:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Latest CW On Flagging</span><hr size=1> /shrug<br>
I don't think AA's matter that much. Get every buff you possibly can, and with the right group set up and intelligent people, you can do it.<br>
<br>
When I was flagged my group was this: Me (warrior), cleric, enchanter, druid, mage, mage. Obviously we had high DPS and were actually able to recover from a few ping pongs by the cleric and mages. However, I've also completed the trials as Me (warrior), cleric, shaman, ranger, paladin, wizard. I've done the trials several times to help people get flagged, very different groups but everyone knew how to play.<br>
<br>
I don't think the point of the trials is so that those with the best gear, weapons, and 500+ AA's can progress. I think they were set in place so that the experienced players (experienced as in jaded) can progress. It might just mean you need to fool around in tier1 zones or keep at the trials until you learn the system.<br>
<br>
Imho.. POV, POS, and BOT are very different than tier1 zones and completely different than any exp zone pre-POP. I think it requires less time exp grinding or raiding then some people think, just more talking to your group and understanding the encounter. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=607776">Veteran Farlander</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - 65 <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior">Overlord</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> on <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/bprexus81531">Prexus</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=farlanderb>FarlanderB</A> at: 3/24/03 12:34:48 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=proteg@thesteelwarrior>proteg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/24/03 12:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Latest CW On Flagging</span><hr size=1> I noticed you have a lot of SS armor, but not like mass amounts of Sleepers gear.  It's nice to know I am not too far away and a couple more nights should do the trick.  <br>
<br>
When the exe comes up, were your casters pretty much oom?  One of our mages said that he heard that the MT needs to kite the exe a bit while the casters med up.  Is this true?  <br>
<br>
Considering most AoE casters are probably flagged already, how is a good way to get a group of AoE'ers?  Get lucky and catch a group of nukers trying to get flagged (meaning stay LFG in PoJ for a while)?  About what level should everyone be?   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gallerus>Gallerus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 188<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/24/03 1:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Latest CW On Flagging</span><hr size=1> When pop 1st came out sometimes we needed to kite the exe.  Now I usually finish exe trial with my cleric around 80m &amp; thats with nuking a lot <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
65 warrior 65 cleric 65 mage 65 mage can easily get any 2 other people through exe trial.<br>
<br>
If you try to kite the exe, need to ditch pets - he casts an ae that will cause pets to attack him &amp; after he takes a certain amount of damage he will summon = no more kiting.<br>
<br>
Its also best to not have the mt kite, since you invariably get hit a few times while kiting, which makes it difficult for the mt to get initial agro without the cleric getting heal agro - usually best to have a druid/ranger or someone else with kiting experience do it - the one time I saw a warrior try to do it was one of hte most pathetic displays i've seen <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.cox.net/mherlihy/img/gallerus.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
