Well, you need ALOT more exp in 61 than 60 so that statement doesnt really make sense... but, don't sit in LCY/LCR those have to be the worst camps in PoD.  Take a group in the rat caves for 2 hours and walk out with 1.5-2 aa's and alot of excitement (I just love harm touches that make me jump in my seat)<br>
<br>
Ive just seen too many people with &quot;similar&quot; armor/lvls/AA's move into PoS/PoV and try for the easy camps and get burnt out or flustrated waiitng hours for an opening in one or two &quot;camps&quot;  :/<br>
<br>
And find a guild or a guilds chat channel, friends make EQ so much more fun. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=proteg@thesteelwarrior>proteg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/24/03 4:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   friends</span><hr size=1> I have been in a decent guild, and have lots of friends.  Takes me very little timw to cobble together a PoP exp group from my friends list and various LFGs that know me.  <br>
<br>
I am not sure how far that will get you for doing stuff like ToV tho.  I hear basically go with a Guild or VERY familiar friends only.  <br>
<br>
Thanks for pointing out good places to exp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=valhalantrueblade>Valhalan Trueblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/25/03 10:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: friends</span><hr size=1> Lvl 60 with 6 aa's will do fine in PoV/PoS. I flagged at Lvl 60 with 6 aa's and Tanked very well in PoV/PoS and suprisingly enough BoT when I hit 62. People were skeptical but you just have to prove them wrong. <br>
<br>
I have very little Velious gear (some PoG Pieces), but I am not under-equipped. <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=89208">www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...?num=89208</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
I did Trials with about 6k HP and 1250ish AC and Did it several times for friends with similar stats. <br>
<br>
The Key is aggro control, DPS and Mana Pool. Clerics over 62 are great to have, their mana pool is usually around 3.5 - 4k. Your Cleric has to have enough mana for you to tank Exe while Casters can med if they need too. Defensive is your friend, if I remember correctly, it dropped his damage from 700+ to 400+ Max and his AE was that nasty AC Debuff.<br>
<br>
Horses for Casters! Cant Stress that enough.<br>
<br>
I have passed Trials as My Warrior and My Wizard. So I know just a wee bit about both aspects. <br>
<br>
I have passed using AE and Single Target. Both work depending on the group structure. <br>
<br>
My Warrior took me over 80 Tries, learning what classes fit best, what tactics got us closest, how best to preserve mana, and timing! <br>
<br>
My Wizard I did in about 5 tries, cause I learned it all on my Warrior. <br>
<br>
Just stick at it and note the elements you use to get you closer and you will make it. I was playing my Wiz with a 59 War Tank in PoV the other night, smart cleric kept him alive, and we all made sure he held aggro. So you will be fine there.<br>
