Have a minimum of 6100 HPs and 1200 AC. Level up to 62 if you want to tank this. If you don't get to 62 then have a 65 warrior, SK or Pally to do the tanking. The higher level you are, the better damage you do and less you take, thus you will also keep aggro better. As of right now, unless you have super uber weapons, you won't do enough damage and your equipment isn't anything to help you tank it well enough. Try to take an enchie instead of a shammy, shammies can get way too much aggro in here, and many shammies just dont have a lot of HPs.<br>
If I were you, I would get a mage around 62, a warrior at 65 a rogue 63 or above and you will be the 4th damage dealer. I have seen a group that was stacked with all 65s including a 65 mage and a 65 monk, fail on this because the tank had 5800 hps and was only level 60. When they changed to a 65 tank and had the 60 tank as additional damage, they passed easily.<br>
Our guild flagging group has me as a 65 warrior, a 61 or 62 mage, a 63-65 rogue, 62-65 cleric, 61-65 enchie and any other class. Our success ratio with this group is about 90-95% or even higher. And yes, that other class has been a cleric at times, so our DPS is already there when we do this. Our mage never casts banish on the rocks when we do it like this.<br>
Have mod rods and use them after the first round always, then use them as soon as they become available again. Tell each caster to stay near you, it actually is possible to have a cleric and the enchie beating on mobs this way, and believe it or not, this can keep them from getting aggro. When you get to boss mob, you should only need 40% mana on the cleric to tank it. If you have considerably less, kite the mob for a little. And like someone else said, kill the pets until mob is engaged. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=proteg@thesteelwarrior>proteg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/25/03 12:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   cool</span><hr size=1> Last try I had two level 57 peeps in the group so that did not work.  Sounds like EVERYONE needs to be 60+, preferrably 61+.  <br>
